UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 341
1 AN ACT relating to school bus stops and declaring an emergency.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 189 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 As used in Sections 1 to 3 of this Act:
6 (1) "Bus stop camera system" means a system of one (1) or more fixed video cameras
7 placed at a school bus stop that is capable of recording and storing video images;
8 (2) "Fund" means the school bus stop safety camera fund established in Section 2 of
9 this Act;
10 (3) "Local government" means a city, county, charter county government, urban-
11 county government, consolidated local government, or unified local government;
12 and
13 (4) "School bus stop":
14 (a) Means a common location near the side of a highway or street where
15 children board and disembark a school bus for a school that is part of a
16 public school district; and
17 (b) Does not include the area in front of a residence where children from that
18 residence board and disembark a school bus.
19 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 189 IS CREATED TO
20 READ AS FOLLOWS:
21 (1) There is hereby established in the State Treasury a trust and agency account to be
22 known as the school bus stop safety camera fund. The fund shall consist of state
23 appropriations, gifts, grants, and federal funds.
24 (2) The fund shall be administered by the Department for Local Government.
25 (3) Amounts deposited in the fund shall be used to provide grants to local
26 governments to install, maintain, and monitor bus stop camera systems positioned
27 at school bus stops and for no other purpose.
