UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 341
1 (4) Notwithstanding KRS 45.229, fund amounts not expended at the close of a fiscal
2 year shall not lapse but shall be carried forward into the next fiscal year.
3 (5) The Department for Local Government shall promulgate administrative
4 regulations in accordance with KRS Chapter 13A to establish application
5 procedures and award criteria for local governments that apply for grants.
6 SECTION 3. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 189 IS CREATED TO
7 READ AS FOLLOWS:
8 (1) A local government:
9 (a) May install a bus stop camera system on public property at any school bus
10 stop within its jurisdiction;
11 (b) May, with the permission of the property owner, install a bus stop camera
12 system on private property at any school bus stop within its jurisdiction;
13 (c) May use grant moneys from the fund to cover the costs of installation,
14 maintenance, and monitoring of bus stop camera systems; and
15 (d) Shall consult with the public school districts in its jurisdiction to determine
16 appropriate locations for placement of bus stop camera systems.
17 (2) On or before August 1, 2026, and on or before August 1 each year thereafter,
18 each public school district shall inform the local governments in whose
19 jurisdictions their schools are located of the location of each school bus stop in
20 the district.
21 (3) (a) Subject to paragraphs (b) and (c) of this subsection, video images from a
22 bus stop camera system shall be retained by the local government that
23 installed the cameras.
24 (b) The parents or guardians of all students assigned to a bus stop where a bus
25 stop camera system is in place shall be given notice and shall have the right
26 to object to video images of their children being retained under this section.
27 (c) If a parent or guardian objects to their children being recorded by a bus
Page 2 of 4
XXXX 2/18/2026 3:10 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 341
1 stop camera system, the faces and personal identifying characteristics of all
2 children assigned to that bus stop shall be redacted or obscured before the
3 video images are used or shared under this section.
4 (4) Video images retained under this section may be obtained only:
5 (a) By a qualifying school district investigating a student discipline matter;
6 (b) By a law enforcement agency; or
7 (c) In response to a subpoena duces tecum.
8 (5) The local government that installed the bus stop camera system shall retain the
9 video images recorded by the system for a period of sixty (60) days and delete the
10 data after that period, except as provided in subsection (6) of this section, or when
11 the data:
12 (a) Is being used as evidence in a felony prosecution;
13 (b) Is being used by a qualifying school district in a student disciplinary matter;
14 (c) Has become subject to a subpoena duces tecum;
15 (d) Is the subject of an evidence protection letter submitted by an attorney
16 licensed in the Commonwealth.
17 (6) In addition to the retention requirements in subsection (5) of this section, if data
18 recorded by the system indicates there is a known injury or collision, the local
19 government that installed the bus stop camera system shall retain the video
20 images recorded by the system for a period of two (2) years and delete the data
21 after that period, except when the data:
22 (a) Is being used as evidence in a felony prosecution;
23 (b) Is being used by a qualifying school district in a student disciplinary matter;
24 (c) Has become subject to a subpoena duces tecum; or
25 (d) Is the subject of an evidence protection letter submitted by an attorney
26 licensed in the Commonwealth.
27 (7) Video images recorded by a bus stop camera system that were retained in
Page 3 of 4
